5. PERFORMANCE ESTIMATES AND COMPARATIVE ANALYSIS

The following table compares the predicted performance of the disclosed invention (Mars‑hardened embodiment) against a conventional fixed‑axis Series Elastic Actuator (SEA) leg operating under identical simulated Martian conditions. The estimates are derived from the analytical models presented in Chapter 3 and assume a rover mass of $m_{body} = 80 \, \text{kg}$.

